<topic id='business_definition_arrival_date_at_accident_and_emergency_department.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Arrival Date at Accident and Emergency Department - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_arrival_date_at_accident_and_emergency_department">Arrival Date At Accident and Emergency Department</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity_date_time">ACTIVITY DATE TIME</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_arrival_date_at_accident_and_emergency_department">Arrival Date At Accident and Emergency Department</xref>
 is the date the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
self presented at the 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_department">Accident and Emergency Department</xref>
 or                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
arrived in an 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_ambulance">Ambulance</xref>
 at the 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_department">Accident and Emergency Department</xref>.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
For the Accident and Emergency Clinical Quality Indicators, for 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 arriving by 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_emergency_ambulance">Emergency Ambulance</xref>, the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_arrival_time_at_accident_and_emergency_department">Arrival Time At Accident and Emergency Department</xref>
 is when handover occurs, or 15 minutes after the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_emergency_ambulance">Emergency Ambulance</xref>
 arrives at the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_department">Accident and Emergency Department</xref>, whichever is the sooner.        </p>
      <p>
Further guidance is available on the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_department_of_health_and_social_care">Department of Health and Social Care</xref>
 National Archives at: 
              <xref href="https://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130105030902/http://www.dh.gov.uk/en/Publicationsandstatistics/Publications/PublicationsPolicyAndGuidance/DH_122868"
               scope="external"
               format="html">A&amp;E clinical quality indicators: Implementation guidance and data definitions</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
